SIMPLE: immune
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Immune
<hw>Im*mune"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>immunis</ets>. See <er>Immunity</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Exempt; protected.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Im*mu"nize</wf>
<pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Protected from disease due to the
action of the immune system, especially by having been inoculated
against or previously exposed to a disease.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the immune
system or the components of the immune system.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Not responsive; <as>as, <ex>immune</ex> to
suggestion</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Immune</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Immune
<hw>Im*mune"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who is immune;
esp., a person who is immune from a disease by reason of previous
affection with the disease or inoculation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>immune system</ent>⟦br⟧
